continued to face power outages after disruptions caused by
freezing rain on Dec. 26, leaving 21,205 people in 140 towns
without electricity as of 6 p.m. yesterday, the Russian
Emergency Ministry said on its website.  OAO MRSK Holding, which manages Russiaâ€™s interregional
